x4freetext: High purity commercial metal foils and
containing the Mo and Mo/Re alloy targets and Ti, Cu
monitor foils were irradiated at low beam
intensities. The activity was measured without
chemical separation by high resolution gamma-ray
spectroscopy. The effective energy for each foil was
determined using the energy-range formula and tables
of Andersen and Ziegler, and corrected by comparing
the simultaneously re-measured cross sections of the
monitor reactions to the latest recommended values.
The activities were determined from the photo-peak
areas, taking into account corrections for decay
during irradiation, waiting and measuring time. Decay
data and the Q-values of the were taken from NUDAT
and from Q-value calculator of NNDC.
The uncertainty of the energy of the
bombarding beam in the middle of each irradiated foil
was estimated combining the uncertainties of the
energy degradation depending on the thickness of the
target foils in the stack and the energy straggling.
The uncertainty of the energy varies between 0.3 MeV
for the first foil and increases up to 1.5 MeV at the
